{
  "texts": [
    "For example, a regression model identifies patterns in continuous data, while a classification model distinguishes between categories, assigning each data item to a specific category.",
    "One ML technique that mimics the structure of the human nervous system is the Neural Network (NN).",
    "Model complexity increases when the output of one NN serves as the input to another in a multi-layered (deep) architecture.",
    "Each unit in such a system can be thought of as having multiple dendrite-like inputs from the previous layer and multiple axon-like outputs to the next layer.",
    "Such systems often self-supervise their learning by estimating labels and adjusting them iteratively to identify salient features or extract meaning in the data."
  ]
}